<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Down Stanford in College Basketball Crown Quarterfinals in Las Vegas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/mens-basketball-mountaineers-rally-to-down-stanford-in-college-basketball-crown-quarterfinals-in-las-vegas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/mens-basketball-mountaineers-rally-to-down-stanford-in-college-basketball-crown-quarterfinals-in-las-vegas</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Morris Ugusuk" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />West Virginia rallied from eight points down with 3:21 left in regulation, and then outscored Stanford 14-9 in the extra session to claim tonight's first quarterfinal-round game 82-77 in the 2026 College Basketball Crown played at MGM Grand Garden Arena in Las Vegas.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg"><media:title>Morris Ugusuk</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Crown-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 23:10:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58958</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia’s Individuals Complete NCAA Regional Competition</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/gymnastics-west-virginias-individuals-complete-ncaa-regional-competition</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/gymnastics-west-virginias-individuals-complete-ncaa-regional-competition</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="emerson smith" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Junior Amber Lowe and sophomores Sophia Rice and Emerson Smith of the West Virginia University gymnastics team completed competition as individual event specialists in the Second Round of the NCAA Regional Championships inside the Maravich Center in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, on Thursday night.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg"><media:title>emerson smith</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/2/Untitled-1-6.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 2 Apr 2026 22:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58957</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Host No. 23 UCF in Battle for First Place</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/baseball-mountaineers-host-no-23-ucf-in-battle-for-first-place</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/2/baseball-mountaineers-host-no-23-ucf-in-battle-for-first-place</guid><category>Baseball</categor